   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>H. Satan s Poisoning of the World 1.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Deceiving the Whole Inhabited Earth</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>See Revelation 12:9 and 20:3.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Doing as He Pleases with the Whole World</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The whole world lies in the evil one, being manipulated and abused by him; this is like a surgical patient on the operation table, lying in the hands of the surgeon, being operated on by him as he wishes.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>See 1 John 5:19.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Being the God of the World</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>and Blinding the Thoughts of the Unbelievers</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>See 2 Corinthians 4:4.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Causing People to Worship Him through Idols</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Satan is behind all the idols.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>All idol-worship is the worship of Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>See Revelation 9:20 and 1 Corinthians 10:20 and compare with Matthew 4:9.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Causing People to Become His Children</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>with His Sinful Life and Evil Nature</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Bible clearly says that those who practice sin are the children of the devil.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The Lord Jesus said, You are of your father the devil John 8:44 .</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The devil s sinful life and evil nature are in his children.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>This is clearly spoken of in 1 John 3:8, John 8:44, and Matthew 23:33.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>6.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Causing People to Practice Sin</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Satan s most prevailing strategy against man is to cause him to practice sin.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>In today s dazzling world of sensual pleasures, everything that man does is sin.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>This is Satan s work.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>See 1 John 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>7.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Snatching the Word Away</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>from the Heart of Men</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>See Matthew 13:19.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>8.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Causing People to Pervert</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>the Ways of the Lord</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>See Acts 13:10.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>9.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Snaring and Catching People Alive</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>See 2 Timothy 2:26.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>10.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Binding People</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Satan binds people with illnesses, demons, the environment, riches, position, fame, and knowledge.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>See Luke 13:16.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>11.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Possessing People</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>See Mark 5:2.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>12.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>Bringing Afflictions to the World</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>The afflictions that are brought to the whole world include wars, natural disasters, man-made calamities, and all kinds of diseases.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>Revelation 12:12 says, Woe to the earth and the sea because the devil has come down to you and has great rage, knowing that he has only a short time.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>When Satan is cast down, great tribulation will begin on the earth; Satan will do all that he can to bring afflictions to the world.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>His heart delights in the hardships and the sufferings of man.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>Whereas God loves man, Satan does evil toward man.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>13.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Deceiving the Nations to War against God</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Revelation 20:3 says that when the thousand years are completed, Satan will be loosed for a little time.</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>His final work will be to deceive the nations of that age to war against God.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
